It's been 4 years, no one has given a replacement for ""Defund the Police"" at all. If it was so easy, and DTP was so miserable surely, folks would have come up with a better alternative by now, right?

Meanwhile, in political circles, it seems to have lent itself to actual attempts at policy changes when allowed to be given the nuance it deserves. It's only talking heads, bad faith actors and people who don't want to engage with the actual meaning who keep talking about it as ""bad branding."" GIRL. It was an activist slogan. How come folks are aware it's not the media's job to carry water for the left, but activists catch flak for doing what activists do?
title: Pod Save America
video_name: Kamala Harris Gets HUGE Surge Of Support + Pete Buttigieg Talks Trump, Vance and The Vice President
description:
And she's off! Kamala Harris has clinched the majority of delegates, she's breaking fundraising records and driving voter registration, and she's out on the trail offering a clear contrast to Donald Trump and his dark vision for America. Tommy and guest host Ali Velshi dissect Harris's campaign rollout, the shifting dynamics of the race, and Benjamin Netanyahu's polarizing address to Congress. Then, Pete Buttigieg—a possible VP pick—joins the show to talk about Harris, JD Vance, and everything he'll be doing to help the ticket win in November.

CHAPTERS
00:00 Intro
01:59 Where Kamala Harris’s Presidential Campaign Stands Right Now
13:58 Trump Campaign’s Response to Harris Campaign
20:29 Right-Wing Voices Attack Kamala Harris
23:32 JD Vance’s Reception Post-RNC 
30:08 Ali Velshi's Story About Trump
32:27 Democratic Veepstakes 
36:04 Biden’s Speech Addressing Decision to Drop Out of Presidential Race
41:53 Interview with Pete Buttigieg
52:50 Benjamin Netanyahu's Address to U.S. Congress
1:06:11 Trump's Troubled Relationship with Bibi Netanyahu
1:10:15 Vice President Harris's Position on Gaza Policy

Crooked believes that we need a better conversation about politics, culture, and the world around us—one that doesn’t just focus on what’s broken, but what we can do to fix it. At a time when it’s increasingly easy to feel cynical or hopeless, former Obama staffers Jon Favreau, Jon Lovett, and Tommy Vietor have created a place where people can have sane conversations that inform, entertain, and inspire action. In 2017 they started Crooked with Pod Save America—a no-bullshit conversation about politics. Since then, we continue to add shows, voices, and opportunities for activism, because it’s up to all of us to do our part to build a better world. That’s it. End of mission.

textOriginal:
Comments JD Vance made in 2021 questioning Vice President Kamala Harris’ leadership because she did not have biological children have resurfaced, testing the young conservative senator in his early days campaigning as part of the Republicans’ presidential ticket.

During Vance’s bid for the Senate in Ohio, he said in a Fox News interview that “we are effectively run in this country via the Democrats,” and referred to them as “a bunch of childless cat ladies who are miserable at their own lives and the choices that they’ve made and so they want to make the rest of the country miserable, too.” He said that included Harris, U.S. Transportation Secretary Pete Buttigieg and U.S. Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez, a New York Democrat.

title: Access Hollywood
video_name: Jennifer Aniston BLASTS Donald Trump’s VP Pick J.D. Vance For ‘Childless’ Women Comment
description:
Jennifer Aniston is sharing her disbelief for Republican Vice-Presidential nominee J.D. Vance’s past comments about “childless” women. After a clip of Donald Trump’s running mate from 2021 resurfaced on social media in which he claims that United States is being run by “childless cat ladies who are miserable at their own lives and choices that they made,” the “Friends” star took to her Instagram story to call him out. “I truly can’t believe this is coming from a potential VP of The United States,” the actress wrote on Wednesday, adding, “All I can say is: Mr. Vance, I pray that your daughter is fortunate enough to bear children of her own one day. I hope she will not need to turn to IVF as a second option. Because you are trying to take that away from her, too.” The “Morning Show” star does not have any children and got candid in a December cover story in 2022 with Allure that she tried to get pregnant for many years but struggled with fertility and IVF.

After a clip of Donald Trump’s running mate from 2021 resurfaced on social media in which he claims that United States is being run by “childless cat ladies who are miserable at their own lives and choices that they made,” the “Friends” star took to her Instagram story to call him out. “I truly can’t believe this is coming from a potential VP of The United States,” the actress wrote on Wednesday, adding, “All I can say is: Mr. Vance, I pray that your daughter is fortunate enough to bear children of her own one day. I hope she will not need to turn to IVF as a second option. Because you are trying to take that away from her, too.” The “Morning Show” star does not have any children and got candid in a December cover story in 2022 with Allure that she tried to get pregnant for many years but struggled with fertility and IVF.

video_name: Jennifer Aniston BLASTS Donald Trump’s VP Pick J.D. Vance For ‘Childless’ Women Comment
description:
Jennifer Aniston is sharing her disbelief for Republican Vice-Presidential nominee J.D. Vance’s past comments about “childless” women. After a clip of Donald Trump’s running mate from 2021 resurfaced on social media in which he claims that United States is being run by “childless cat ladies who are miserable at their own lives and choices that they made,” the “Friends” star took to her Instagram story to call him out. “I truly can’t believe this is coming from a potential VP of The United States,” the actress wrote on Wednesday, adding, “All I can say is: Mr. Vance, I pray that your daughter is fortunate enough to bear children of her own one day. I hope she will not need to turn to IVF as a second option. Because you are trying to take that away from her, too.” The “Morning Show” star does not have any children and got candid in a December cover story in 2022 with Allure that she tried to get pregnant for many years but struggled with fertility and IVF.

title: Access Hollywood
video_name: Jennifer Aniston BLASTS Donald Trump’s VP Pick J.D. Vance For ‘Childless’ Women Comment
description:
Jennifer Aniston is sharing her disbelief for Republican Vice-Presidential nominee J.D. Vance’s past comments about “childless” women. After a clip of Donald Trump’s running mate from 2021 resurfaced on social media in which he claims that United States is being run by “childless cat ladies who are miserable at their own lives and choices that they made,” the “Friends” star took to her Instagram story to call him out. “I truly can’t believe this is coming from a potential VP of The United States,” the actress wrote on Wednesday, adding, “All I can say is: Mr. Vance, I pray that your daughter is fortunate enough to bear children of her own one day. I hope she will not need to turn to IVF as a second option. Because you are trying to take that away from her, too.” The “Morning Show” star does not have any children and got candid in a December cover story in 2022 with Allure that she tried to get pregnant for many years but struggled with fertility and IVF.
